main event: A possible satellite was observed in the Pacific Ocean on May 5, 1964 at coordinates 43.10 N 174 W.
interesting points: The object was observed by air and reported as an air-visual sighting.
The object was traveling on a course of 060 degrees and had an intensity of a first magnitude star.
The report indicates the object may have been a satellite, but satellite schedules were not available to confirm this.
The sighting was reported through a CIRVIS (Communications Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report.
The sighting was evaluated as unknown, and the report was retransmitted to the CIA, DIA, and other agencies.
